### 🎨 UI Standards

#### UI Manager Pattern
```csharp
// ✅ UI managers should register and find dependencies
public class UIManager : MonoBehaviour
{
    private GameManager gameManager;
    
    private void Awake()
    {
        DependencyRegistry.Register<UIManager>(this);
    }
    
    private void Start()
    {
        gameManager = DependencyRegistry.Find<GameManager>();
        
        if (gameManager != null)
        {
            gameManager.OnScoreChanged += UpdateScore;
        }
    }
}
```

#### Button Handlers
```csharp
// ✅ Clean up button listeners
private void OnDestroy()
{
    if (playButton != null)
    {
        playButton.onClick.RemoveAllListeners();
    }
}
```

---

### 📝 Documentation Standards

#### XML Documentation
```csharp
// ✅ Always document public methods and properties
/// <summary>
/// Adds points to the current score
/// </summary>
/// <param name="points">The number of points to add</param>
public void AddScore(int points)
{
    // Implementation
}
```

#### Code Comments
```csharp
// ✅ Use clear, descriptive comments
// Register with dependency registry for cross-scene access
DependencyRegistry.Register<GameManager>(this);

// ❌ Avoid obvious comments
// score = 0; // Set score to zero
```

